HEADWORD: Mewl
<hw>Mewl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Mewled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mewling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>miauler</ets> to
mew, E. <ets>mew</ets> to cry as a cat. Cf. <er>Miaul</er>.]</ety>
<def>To cry, as a young child; to squall.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>meawl</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

